<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">infer</ENAMEX> ought from is --to commit the "naturalistic fallacy"--only
leads to moral confusion. For example, you might, after observing the natural
behavior of praying mantises, be tempted to conclude that it is morally good
for <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">females</ENAMEX> to eat <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">males</ENAMEX> after sex--and this, I submit, would be a repugnant
